I"»<p>Manim installation has become quite straghtforward since the <code class="highlighter-rouge">manimlib</code> wheel was released on <code class="highlighter-rouge">pip</code>.
The system dependencies are as follows:</p>
<ol>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">cario</code>: 2D graphics library</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">latex</code>: A high-quality typesetting system</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">ffmpeg</code>: Rendering videos</li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">sox</code>: Sound Processing</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="installing-system-dependencies">Installing System Dependencies</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Fedora
  <code class="highlighter-rouge">sudo dnf install cairo-devel ffmpeg sox texlive-scheme-full</code></li>
  <li>Ubuntu
  <code class="highlighter-rouge">
  sudo apt install libcairo2-dev ffmpeg sox texlive texlive-fonts-extra texlive-latex-extra texlive-latex-recommended texlive-science tipa</code></li>
</ul>
